title: For Sale:  Taurus PT809
postcontent:
I have a very lightly used Taurus PT809 for sale, I am asking $400. This gun has about 50 rounds put through it. As the model number indicates it is in 9mm caliber with 17+1 capacity. While you can do your own research on the pistol, I will list some of its features. This pistol is based off the the Taurus 24/7 OSS model Taurus tried to design for the military. It is a hammer fired DA/SA with a 3 position safety. You can carry it cocked and locked, uncocked and locked, or safety off in DA. Depressing the safety downward decocks the hammer. It has has 3 dot novak sights, and accessory rail. It is a polymer framed gun with a black tennifer finish which is similar to the glock finish or the SA XD melonite finish. 

I have the gun, the original case, a mag loader, Taurus security system keys, 2 mags total, 3 back-straps (small, medium, large), and all the paper work. Like all Taurus guns it has a lifetime warranty. 

I bought this gun for my wife, but here hands are too small. I thought the smallest backstrap would solve this problem, but its still to large. If you have smaller hands hands this is not the pistol for you. SA is fine, but the DA trigger length of pull is almost too long for me. I also have smaller hands for a guy.

title: For Sale/Trade:  IOM Prototype
postcontent:
I have to sell or trade a very rear and hard to find IOM Prototype.  It's a very collectable piece for the Five_seveN enthusiast and comes with all the original components. $2000 Firm.

There have been several variants before the current USG model that everyone is aware of. First FN came out with a DAO model, then the Tactical, IOM and finally the USG. 

The IOM prototype was a very small run of modified Tacticals that were made for the IOM trials. It is the rarest version of FsN made. It did not come with a letter as it was pre-IOM and these were not made for sale to anyone, Officers or the public. After the trial they were given to some special people.

You can tell an "IOM" Prototype from a military/law enforcement only Tactical by first, the serial number is in IOM format (3861xxxxx), not Tactical format (386Mxxxxx). Secondly, the serial is embedded in a metal strip above the accessory rail instead of silk-screened onto the frame above the grip. Finally, the IOM Prototype has adjustable low profile rear sight where the LE/Military Tactical had small, fixed sights and the magazine capacity was reduced to ten rounds by epoxying in a block of plastic in the bottom of the stack.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Gun Collection For Sale or Possible Trade
postcontent:
Up for sale are a few firearms that I never use or use very seldom. The majority of these guns were purchased new by me and the majority of them have never been fired. I simply bought them and put them in the safe. I posted these before and had a sudden change of heart and decided not to sell them. However, my wife and I have found some property that we would like to purchase. So I am listing these for sale again. I may consider trades as well. Multiple guns trades are ok. I have a variety of interests when it comes to firearms so please make offers. I will consider trades plus cash as well. It really just depends on what you have. I am an ak guy by heart but will consider other trades as well. Below is a list of all of the guns that I am offering for sale or trade. There is also a variety of ammunition for sale as well. I also have a very extensive and valuable collection of autographs for sale. This is my personal collection and I have put this collection together over the years. This is an amazing collection for any baseball fan. The total autograph collection is valued at over $20,000. I also have these items listed below. All of the autographs have proper documentation and certificates of authenticity. I prefer cash but I will consider trades on these items as well. My asking price for the entire collection is $5,500. However, I will consider any reasonable offer. I must sell these items rather quickly because I do not want the property that we are planning on purchasing to be sold. We really need the money for a larger down payment. I will consider trades and cash offers, but please be reasonable. Thanks for looking. 

GUNS: 

Custom Saiga 12 Guage Shotgun
Price: $1350
This gun is absolutely amazing. If you are looking for the ultimate SHTF gun then this is exactly what you are looking for. This gun was custom built to my specs by Mach 1 Arsenal out of Tennessee. This gun features many upgrades and is 922 compliant. This gun has been equipped with a SGM Tactical tri mail, Razor Shark break, SGM Tactial stock, adjustable cheek rest, single point sling mount, finger groove pistol grip, also comes with 12 round SGM Tactical magazine. I will include a 20 round MD arms drum as well for an additional $50. This gun has never been fired. I purchased it directly from Mach 1 Arsenal and put it in my safe. This is a beautiful weapon and will make someone extremely happy. This is definitely not your everyday converted Saiga.

Winchester 94 AE Lever Action 30/30
Price: $425
This is a nearly prefect example of Winchester's famous lever action rifle. This 94 AE is chambered in 30/30 and has seen very little usage. I have fired this rifle very little and used it as a brush gun during hunting season only a few select times. This gun is in excellent condition and is the closest thing that you will find to new. 

Remington 770 30/06 bolt action rifle
Price: $325
I purchased this rifle a few years ago and never actually fired the rifle. I took it out one time with me hunting but never had the opportunity to fire it. This rifle is chambered in 30/06 and comes with a 3-9x40 scope mounted. The scope has never even been sighted in. It also has a camo sling mounted. This would make a perfect deer rifle for someone. 

DPMS AR-15 20" A2 target rifle with stainless bull barrel
Price: $1,050
This rifle is the most accurate AR that I have ever shot. This is a DPMS AR-15 with an A2 stock and a 20 inch long, 1 inch diameter stainless bull barrel. This rifle has a free floating barrel and a free floating DPMS handguard, forward assist, and dust covers. The rifle also has a 6-24x44 scope that has not been sighted in. The scope has been mounted on a top rail scope mount. The rifle also has a bipod mounted. This rifle has a railed gas block and will come with two magazines as well. The stock has a few knicks and dings but nothing major. This came from shooting on a bench. The gun has been fired very little and hasn't been fired since I mounted the scope. 

Glock 22 40 S&W in OD Green
Price:$500
This is a brand new Glock and has never been fired. This is a Gen 3 glock and will come with two factory hi-capacity glock mags. I purchased this gun when I learned that Glock would no longer release any OD green glocks. I can include a blackhawk carbon fiber holster and two KCI extreme capacity glock mags for an additional $75. I believe they are 31 rounders but I am not positive. The last OD green gen 3 glock that was new in the box sold for over $500 with $25 shipping plus ffl fees on Gunbroker. This is going to be a collector's item very soon. Especially in unfired condition. 

Sig Sauer Platinum Elite 1911
Price:$1100
This is the most beautiful 1911 that you have ever seen. This pistol has never been fired. I purchased it about a year ago and placed it in my safe. This gun has night sites installed. Checkered grip, beavertail grip safety, and many other custom features. This is a beautiful pistol and would make an excellent carry weapon or one to put up as an heirloom. This is the highest end of Sig Sauer 1911's and they are getting harder and harder to find. Comes with 2 sig sauer factory mags.

Sig Sauer 2022 9mm
Price:$450
This gun is brand new in the box and has never been fired. I purchased this gun and put it in my safe. This gun is chambered in 9mm and is meant to outlast most of your other standard 9mm pistols. This will come with an extra grip that fits larger hands and one high capacity magazine. This is a compact carry gun that is in new condition. Reliability will never be an issue with this pistol. I own another of this model and have shot it regularly. It is a great pistol for the money. 

I will follow the law when selling any of my pistols or rifles. Please do not try to buy a gun from me if you are a felon or cannot possess a firearm. 


Autograph Collection
Price: $5500 or best offer

This collection is valued at over $20,000. I have much much more than my asking price invested in this collection. I am simply trying to move this collection quickly in order to put a down payment on a piece of property. I may consider trades on a few items but I really prefer cash on these autographs. I would like to sell the entire collection all at once because time is limited on my end. This would be perfect for someone to resale on ebay or for an avid collector. I simply don't have the time to sell these items individually so the first person with a reasonable cash offer will take the entire collection. I am only asking $5500 for the entire collection.
